{"word":"Obed","slug":"obed","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Obed</b> <a href=\"#/H5744\">H5744</a><br/><a href=\"#/G5601\">G5601</a> <br/> 1. Son of Boaz and grandfather of David<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=8&chapter=4&verse=22'>Rth 4:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=2&verse=12'>1Ch 2:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=1&verse=5'>Mat 1:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=3&verse=32'>Luk 3:32</a><br/> 2. Son of Ephlal and grandson of Zabad<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=2&verse=38'>1Ch 2:38</a><br/> 3. One of David's heroes<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=47'>1Ch 11:47</a><br/> 4. Son of Shemaiah. A gatekeeper of the temple<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=26&verse=7'>1Ch 26:7</a><br/> 5. Father of Azariah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=23&verse=1'>2Ch 23:1</a>"}]}